HK bond market seen attracting int ' l issuers - HSBC . Hong Kong ' s debt capital markets will continue to attract regional and international borrowers , Anita Fung , head of Hong Kong dollar bond markets at Hongkong Bank ' s HSBC Markets said on Monday . " We will see more issuers both within the region or globally that will be interested in tapping the Hong Kong dollar debt market in different tenors , " Fung said at a debt conference in Hong Kong . Fung noted that U . S . mortgage agency Fannie Mae last week launched the first - ever Hong Kong - dollar denominated global bond issue . Other AAA - rated issuers , such as the World Bank , also have tapped the Hong Kong dollar market . Hong Kong is one of the most sophisticated financial centers in Asia outside Japan , with over US $ 103 billion in funds under management at the end of 1996 , Fung said . The government debt market is well developed . The yield curve for Exchange Fund Notes extends out to 10 years , among the longest in Asia , and is expected to be extended further . The yield spread between Hong Kong dollar and U . S . dollar bonds has been narrowing over the last several years , reflecting a waning of the risk premium for Hong Kong paper . " The reduction of the spread or the risk premium is a vote of confidence from investors on the currency and financial well - being of the economy , " said Fung . Asia ' s huge funding needs for infrastructure development are expected to drive development of local bond markets , including Hong Kong ' s . Fung noted that the World Bank has estimated Asia ' s infrastructure funding needs at US $ 8 trillion between 1994 and 2000 . - - Hong Kong Newsroom ( 852 ) 2847 4039 
